{"word":"ἀκοή","slug":"ἀκοή","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἀϰοή, ῆς, ἡ</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀκούω\">ἀκούω</a></el>]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp> <i>hearing</i><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> as sensory faculty <b><a href='B:530 12:17'>1 Cor 12:17</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> as act <b><a href='B:680 2:8'>2 Pt 2:8</a>;</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <b><a href='B:470 13:14'>Mt 13:14</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>c.</pp></b> as organ of hearing = <i>ear</i> <b><a href='B:480 7:35'>Mk 7:35</a>; <a href='B:510 17:20'>Ac 17:20</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> ‘that which is heard’<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp> <i>fame, report</i> <a href='B:470 4:24'>Mt 4:24</a>; <a href='B:470 14:1'>14:1</a>; <i>rumor</i> <a href='B:470 24:6'>24:6</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp> <i>message, proclamation</i> <a href='B:500 12:38'>J 12:38</a>; <a href='B:520 10:16'>Ro 10:16f</a>; <a href='B:550 3:2'>Gal 3:2</a>, <a href='B:550 3:5'>5</a>; <a href='B:590 2:13'>1 Th 2:13</a>; <a href='B:650 4:2'>Hb 4:2</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀκμήν\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀκολουθέω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}